6:
Good work, team! That was one of our 
best pushes yet. We'll conquer that 
Kaleidoscope yet!
8:
I KNEW it was the right call to join you 
guys! You're all the best!
11:
Eh, I didn't do anything special. It was 
thanks to your knowledge that we got 
as far as we did.
15:
Don't sell yourself short, Alk! 
You oughta be proud of your 
contributions!
18:
I saw you supporting all of us back in 
there like a boss. You're a vital part of 
the team!
25: Heh... I'm glad you guys think so.
31:
Are you okay with just leaving things 
like that?
35:
You mean with Ash? He's probably not 
too happy with how things ended up, 
but it's for the best.
38:
And in any case, I was the one who 
turned him down. Apologizing to him 
now wouldn't do any good.
41:
Yeah... He's probably embarrassed 
enough as it is.
44:
Is there a reason you won't work with 
someone like him?
48:
Beyond the Midways is when things 
get super deadly, right? It's too dicey 
for someone like him.
51:
Yeah, but to be fair, the Midways and 
Depths are dicey for anyone. Right?
54:
Exactly right. The difference is that 
YOU guys recognize that.
57:
A lot of adventurers get cocky and 
bite off more than they can chew. 
Like Ash.
58: I... can't work with people like that.
61:
You can call it selfish or whatever, 
but I want to conquer the 
Kaleidoscope ONLY if everyone's 
survival is guaranteed.
65:
I have the utmost faith that you'll 
succeed, Ellya.
70:
Hehe... I knew you'd get it, Stella. 
Thanks, girl!
74:
Anywho! Back to business—let's talk 
about our next big step.
85:
Once the Kaleidoscope's been 
squared off, I wanna set up a new 
organization to run things around 
here—really give the Guild a run for its 
money, you know?
89: Hoo, boy... here we go again.
95: Alllllk, are you listeniiing to meee?
100:
Huh? Oh, yes, yes. Of course I'm—Wait, 
who gave Ellya something to drink?!
103: I suppose I shouldn't have done that.
109:
SERIOUSLY, I don't get the Guild 
sometimes. Like, how you gonna 
throw a bunch of kids into the 
Kaleidoscope without at least training 
them, right?
119:
*gulp* Ahh! I'm telling ya, the guild's 
days are numbered! I'll show 'em how 
to REALLY run... things...
128:
*sigh* The apple doesn't fall far from 
the tree, huh?
131:
Ellya's father was an adventurer just 
like her—the guy couldn't hold his 
liquor either.
132:
But one day... he never came back 
from the Kaleidoscope. He was a 
fearless one, that's for sure.
137:
Ellya... She was just a kid. I know she 
can be a lot sometimes, but please do 
look after her.
146:
Urgh... my head is pounding. What the 
hell happened yesterday?
154:
I'll put on some shellfish soup. 
It'll do wonders for your hangover.
159:
After you feel a little better, come and 
join us for some training.
165:
I mean... that Kaleidoscope isn't 
gonna conquer itself, right?
168:
But we're in no hurry to dig ourselves 
an early grave either.
174:
U-uh, okay? What are you guys going 
on about all of a sudden?
178: Come on, we're going to Starview!
183:
I'm glad you're all gung ho about this 
suddenly, but...
